I'm running into a JS_Parse_Error during the Gulp uglify-angular task... Anybody else having this issue?
Gulp Output
. Found my issue... For anybody else running into the JS_Parse_Error, here's a fix, and how I found it.
Looks like a trailing . made it's way into the bottom of js/angular/directives/notifications.js. Simply removing that . on line 61 solved my build issue.
I used gulp-util to find it:
1. Install Gulp-util
2. Import the Gulp-util by adding gutil = require('gulp-util'), to the var declarations in your gulpfile.js
3. Attach the error handler to the uglify task: .on('error', gutil.log). The updated task looks like this:
``` javascript
// Process Angular JS
gulp.task('uglify-angular', function() {
  var libs = [
    'bower_components/angular/angular.js',
    'bower_components/angular-animate/angular-animate.js',
    'bower_components/ui-router/release/angular-ui-router.js',
    'js/angular/*/.js',
  ];
return gulp.src(libs)
    .pipe(uglify({
      beautify: true,
      mangle: false
    })).on('error', gutil.log)
    .pipe(concat('angular-app.js'))
    .pipe(gulp.dest('./build/assets/js/'))
  ;
});
```
Hope this helps... And hopefully that trailing . was not intentional and just not parsing correctly on my machine :bow:
