WojciechLuczkow:
Hi, I faced similiar issue, thats how I got it fixed:
In popup directive add another function destroy:
javascript
scope.destroy = function() {
    scope.active = false;
    if(tetherInit) {
        tether.destroy();
        $(element[0]).remove();
        tetherInit = false;
    }
};
also in postLink I have added cleanup(should be there anyway):
javascript
element.on('$destroy', function() {
    foundationApi.unsubscribe(attrs.id);
});
Now when I switch view using UI router in onExit I am publishing 'destroy' message to the popup
